    {
      "id": "5a93c517_27c19ae4",
      "file_path": "services/activity-spec/activity-spec-web/activity-spec-service/src/main/java/org/openecomp/activityspec/errors/ActivitySpecErrorResponse.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 21,
      "message": "Well the point is that 'data' annotation is equal to:\n@Getter\n@Setter\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\n@ToString\n@EqualsAndHashCode\n\n\nand since it's a response it should be immutable. So you shouldn't need any setters. Also without any final od @NotNull fields @RequiredArgsConstructor should be equal to empty constructor which you provided.\n\nhttps://github.com/rzwitserloot/lombok/blob/master/src/core/lombok/Data.java",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3541,
        "name": "Adam Krysiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "adam.krysiak@nokia.com",
        "username": "akrysiak"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-23 13:12:23.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_c78236c8",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_80508f5f",
      "file_path": "services/activity-spec/activity-spec-web/activity-spec-service/src/main/java/org/openecomp/activityspec/errors/ActivitySpecErrorResponse.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 21,
      "message": "This is only partially correct. These classes are used by another mechanism that relies on a default constructor and setters. So making the class immutable will break stuff. For now we are introducing Lombok in order to avoid writing setters/getters manually. Equals and toString are a bonus. We'll reconsider immutability as soon as the mechanism that relies on setters has been fixed.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-26 06:25:19.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_27c19ae4",
      "unresolved": false
    },
